kingdom as part of the takeover conditions for the acquisition hsbc holdings plc was required to relocate its world headquarters from hong kong to london in  major acquisitions in south america started with the purchase of the banco bamerindus of brazil for bn in march  and the acquisition of roberts sa de inversiones of argentina for m in may  in may  hsbc expanded its presence in the united states with the purchase of republic national bank of new york for bn  to edit the hsbc main building in hong kong which was designed by norman foster and completed in  expansion into continental europe took place in april  with the acquisition of cr√©dit commercial de france a large french bank for ¬£bn in july  hsbc bought demirbank an insolvent turkish bank in july  arthur andersen announced that hsbc usa inc through a new subsidiary wealth and tax advisory services usa inc wtas would purchase a portion of andersens tax practice the new hsbc private client services group would serve the wealth and tax advisory needs of highnetworth individuals then in august  hsbc acquired grupo financiero bital sa de cv mexicos third largest retail bank for bn in november  hsbc expanded further in the united states under the chairmanship of sir john bond it spent ¬£ billion us billion to acquire household finance corporation hfc a us credit card issuer and subprime lender in a  cover story the banker noted when banking historians look back they may conclude that it was the deal of the first decade of the st century under the new name of hsbc finance the division was the second largest subprime lender in the us on  november  the hongkong and shanghai banking corp would provide a fixedrate mortgage to buyers of cheung kong holdings victoria towers residential development the new headquarters of hsbc holdings at  canada square london officially opened in april  in september  hsbc bought polski kredyt bank sa of poland for m in june  hsbc expanded into china buying  of the bank of communication